1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:58,470 --> 00:01:59,350
Huh?

3
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:00,600
That was way off!

4
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:02,350
What are you up to?

5
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:04,480
Cannon practice!

6
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,360
But this thing doesn't shoot right.

7
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:09,570
I'm telling you, let me try!

8
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:12,860
Based on the last shot's trajectory...

9
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:14,030
That should do it.

10
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:15,410
Fire!

11
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:18,030
Awesome!

12
00:02:18,370 --> 00:02:19,830
You hit it on your first try!

13
00:02:19,830 --> 00:02:21,500
I really hit it...

14
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:22,870
Wh-What do you think?!

15
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:24,670
I always hit what I aim at!

16
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:26,500
Impressed?!

17
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:26,500
Yeah! Yeah!

18
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:29,130
It's settled! You're our marksman!

19
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:31,380
What?! I don't get to be the captain?!

20
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:33,470
I'm the captain!

21
00:02:34,430 --> 00:02:37,350
Well, whatever!
I'll humor you for now!

22
00:02:37,350 --> 00:02:40,850
But if you do anything cowardly,
I'm taking over immediately!

23
00:02:40,850 --> 00:02:41,850
Yeah, that's fine.

24
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:44,270
But anyway, I was thinking,

25
00:02:44,270 --> 00:02:47,980
we need to fill one more position
before going to the Grand Line!

26
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:50,940
Good idea! We do
have a fancy kitchen!

27
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:52,820
Though if you pay me, I can do it.

28
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:54,780
They're a necessity on long journeys!

29
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:57,490
Yeah! All pirate ships
need one, right?!

30
00:02:58,070 --> 00:02:59,330
A musician!

31
00:02:59,330 --> 00:03:00,700
Are you stupid?!

32
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,950
What do you think a voyage is?!

33
00:03:02,950 --> 00:03:05,330
I thought you'd say
something smart for once...

34
00:03:05,670 --> 00:03:08,580
Pirates need to sing, you know!

35
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:13,420
Get out here, pirate scum!

36
00:03:15,010 --> 00:03:16,630
What?! What?!

37
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:17,680
Who are you?!

38
00:03:18,260 --> 00:03:20,560
Shut the hell up!

39
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,680
Who I am doesn't concern you!

40
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,770
How many are there?

41
00:03:26,770 --> 00:03:28,980
One... I think?

42
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:31,110
Then he can handle it.

43
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:35,150
We've taken the heads
of many a pirate!

44
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:39,620
Are you wannabe pirates
trying to kill my partner?!

45
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,030
That voice...

46
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:43,040
What do you mean, "partner"?!

47
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,620
I dunno what's going on,

48
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:47,500
but stop breaking our ship!

49
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:50,210
Lost...

50
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:53,420
Lost by a hair...

51
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:56,010
What's going on?

52
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:59,800
Hey! Is that you, Johnny?!

53
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:03,430
Who the hell are you
to say my name?!

54
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:07,810
B-Big Bro Zoro?!

55
00:04:07,810 --> 00:04:09,310
It is you, Johnny!

56
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:11,230
Why are you on a pirate ship?!

57
00:04:11,770 --> 00:04:12,980
Is something wrong?

58
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:14,190
Where's Yosaku?

59
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:14,940
Well...

60
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:20,620
What? Does Zoro know that guy?

61
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:21,990
What's going on?

62
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,000
Y-Yosaku is...

63
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,300
He's sick?

64
00:04:36,170 --> 00:04:40,510
He was fine until a few days ago...

65
00:04:40,890 --> 00:04:43,760
when all of a sudden,
he went pale and kept fainting.

66
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,810
I have no idea what's causing it.

67
00:04:47,770 --> 00:04:52,980
Eventually, teeth started falling out,
and an old wound opened up.

68
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:55,860
I didn't know what to do anymore.

69
00:04:56,360 --> 00:05:00,530
So, I took him to rest
on a rocky islet. But then...

70
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:10,080
a cannonball came
flying from this ship...

71
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:23,340
– W-We're sorry!
– W-We're sorry!

72
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,970
Sorry doesn't quite cut it.

73
00:05:30,180 --> 00:05:31,440
Isn't that right,

74
00:05:31,890 --> 00:05:33,480
partner?

75
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,570
Big Bro, is he...

76
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:39,360
going to die?

77
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:45,700
Are you all stupid?

78
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:46,700
What'd you say?!

79
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,580
Wh-What're you doing?!

80
00:05:53,290 --> 00:05:54,580
Ouch!

81
00:05:54,580 --> 00:05:58,170
If you mock my partner's
death, you'll pay for–

82
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:01,720
Luffy! Usopp! You know
the limes in the hold?

83
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:03,220
Are you listening?!

84
00:06:03,550 --> 00:06:05,390
Bring them here. Now!

85
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:06,430
– Yes ma'am!
– Yes ma'am!

86
00:06:06,970 --> 00:06:09,390
Out of my way!

87
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:09,390
Out of my way!

88
00:06:19,110 --> 00:06:20,480
It's scurvy.

89
00:06:21,030 --> 00:06:22,650
Scurvy?

90
00:06:22,650 --> 00:06:25,820
If we caught it in time,
he'll be fine in a few days.

91
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:28,280
R-Really, Big Sis?!

92
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,790
Big Sis, is he really–

93
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:34,120
Stop... calling me that.

94
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:40,050
Back in the day, that disease
was the bane of sailors everywhere.

95
00:06:40,050 --> 00:06:43,260
– Here, drink it. Drink a lot.
– Here... drink more. Drink more.

96
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:48,180
But the cause was simply
a deficiency of plant-based nutrients.

97
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:53,140
Back then, ships didn't carry
fresh produce since it didn't keep.

98
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:55,350
Okay, now. Put them all in his mouth!

99
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:56,440
Now he'll be fine.

100
00:06:58,020 --> 00:06:59,770
You're amazing!

101
00:06:59,770 --> 00:07:01,530
You're like a doctor!

102
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:06,660
Well, I always thought
you were a can-do kind of girl.

103
00:07:06,990 --> 00:07:08,700
You should already know that!

104
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:11,490
One day it could kill you!

105
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:16,460
Wha...

106
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:18,880
– Yay! Yay! Yay!
– Yay! Yay! Yay!

107
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,630
Those nutrients brought me back!

108
00:07:20,630 --> 00:07:22,550
Alright, partner!

109
00:07:22,550 --> 00:07:25,510
You shouldn't feel better that fast!

110
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:31,010
– Sorry for the late introduction.
– Sorry for the late introduction.

111
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:32,850
My name is Johnny.

112
00:07:33,470 --> 00:07:34,980
I'm Yosaku.

113
00:07:35,690 --> 00:07:39,860
– The pirate bounty hunter duo!
– The pirate bounty hunter duo!

114
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:42,690
We used to work with Big Bro Zoro.

115
00:07:42,690 --> 00:07:44,650
Glad to make your acquaintance.

116
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:50,410
I never thought
I'd see you guys here.

117
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:52,700
We're just as surprised as you are.

118
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:56,080
Hard to believe Pirate Hunter Zoro
would become a pirate himself.

119
00:07:57,460 --> 00:07:58,120
Yeah, I know.

120
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:00,250
Big Bro!

121
00:08:06,550 --> 00:08:08,800
H-Hey, partner?!

122
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:19,230
Let this be a lesson.

123
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:20,310
Yeah.

124
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:23,820
There are pitfalls like this
on extended voyages.

125
00:08:23,820 --> 00:08:30,200
We'll have to balance our nutrition
using the limited food we have on board.

126
00:08:30,530 --> 00:08:34,410
If you think about it,
it's a required skill set...

127
00:08:36,790 --> 00:08:39,040
A required skill set, huh?

128
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,880
Okay, then! A seafaring cook!

129
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,040
– What?
– What?

130
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:45,130
Let's go find a seafaring cook!

131
00:08:45,130 --> 00:08:49,590
That's it! Then we'll be able
to eat well even at sea!

132
00:08:49,590 --> 00:08:52,550
Exactly!

133
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:57,640
If you're looking for a cook
like that, I know just the place.

134
00:08:58,310 --> 00:09:03,520
But the Grand Line is
just around the corner.

135
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:05,690
While there,

136
00:09:05,690 --> 00:09:08,690
you might even hear rumors
about the hawk-eyed man.

137
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:11,910
Set course for...

138
00:09:12,740 --> 00:09:14,620
north-northeast!

139
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:16,830
Alright!

140
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:29,010
Our destination is...

141
00:09:35,930 --> 00:09:37,560
the Sea Restaurant...

142
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,640
Baratie!

143
00:09:44,610 --> 00:09:47,270
What do you think, everyone?!

144
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,900
It's a huge fish!

145
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:51,030
How lovely!

146
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,860
That's pretty funky!

147
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:56,450
Right?! Just like I told you, right?!

148
00:09:59,910 --> 00:10:01,500
Wh-What the...

149
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,670
What's a Marine ship doing...

150
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:07,380
in a place like this?!

151
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:13,680
Th-There's no way they'd
shoot at us, would they?

152
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,850
Wh-When did they show up?!

153
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:21,180
I've never seen that pirate flag.

154
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:23,310
Darn it!

155
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:26,520
W-We're not pirates!

156
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,230
Yeah!

157
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,690
I'm from Marine Headquarters!

158
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,530
Lieutenant Ironfist Fullbody!

159
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:36,780
Hey, which of you is the captain?!

160
00:10:36,780 --> 00:10:38,280
Identify yourself!

161
00:10:38,660 --> 00:10:40,540
I'm Luffy!

162
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:42,830
I'm Usopp!

163
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:46,790
We just made our pirate flag
the day before yesterday!

164
00:10:46,790 --> 00:10:49,590
And I'm the one who drew it!

165
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:53,720
What's with these boneheads?

166
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:59,760
And I know I've seen
you two somewhere before.

167
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:03,350
If memory serves, you're a pair of
small-time bounty hunters.

168
00:11:03,350 --> 00:11:04,270
Wh-What?!

169
00:11:04,690 --> 00:11:08,520
So you finally got caught by pirates?

170
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,940
W-We are...

171
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,070
That's a laugh.

172
00:11:13,070 --> 00:11:15,240
C'mon, let's get going.

173
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:15,780
Yeah.

174
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:20,950
You think small-time bounty hunters
would go after these guys?!

175
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:26,960
Now, let's head into the restaurant.

176
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:30,040
They're an eyesore.

177
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:31,710
Sink them.

178
00:11:31,710 --> 00:11:32,630
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

179
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:39,930
He ignored us.

180
00:11:39,930 --> 00:11:42,430
Next time we see him,
we'll shut him up!

181
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:44,850
What is this?

182
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:48,020
It's our collection of
wanted posters, Big Sis Na–

183
00:11:51,980 --> 00:11:55,950
Basically, if we take them down,
we'll get the reward money.

184
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:58,360
A profitable business.
Right, Big Sis?

185
00:12:05,620 --> 00:12:07,080
Th-This is bad!

186
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,040
H-Hey! They're aiming right at us!

187
00:12:14,170 --> 00:12:15,130
Leave it to me!

188
00:12:15,550 --> 00:12:18,760
Gum-Gum...

189
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,850
Slingshot!

190
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:52,880
Chef!

191
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,630
Are you all right, Chef Zeff?!

192
00:12:54,630 --> 00:12:56,550
Chef, are you okay?!

193
00:13:00,050 --> 00:13:01,970
Are you really okay, Chef Zeff?!

194
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:04,600
I'm saying I'm not okay!

195
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:09,440
Never mind, just return to
the restaurant and get to work!

196
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:12,310
B-But Chef Zeff, your wounds...!

197
00:13:12,310 --> 00:13:13,360
You idiots!

198
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,730
Are you trying to piss me off?!

199
00:13:16,110 --> 00:13:19,360
Feeding customers is a cook's job!

200
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:23,700
Do you morons want to put
my restaurant out of business?!

201
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,620
We got him, Chef.

202
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:32,370
He's the one responsible.

203
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:38,460
I-I-I-I'm very sorry!

204
00:13:42,630 --> 00:13:43,470
Your leg...!

205
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:45,300
Dumbass!

206
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:48,020
Oh, so it was already like that.

207
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:55,520
But I'm all banged up thanks to you.

208
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:59,860
The medical fees and the repairs
for the ship will cost you a fortune!

209
00:14:02,820 --> 00:14:04,700
I won't ask you to lower the charges.

210
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,870
Oh?

211
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:06,830
But...

212
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:08,870
I don't have money!

213
00:14:10,870 --> 00:14:13,210
You've gotta be kidding me.

214
00:14:13,710 --> 00:14:15,750
Well, if you don't have money,

215
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,750
your only choice is to work here.

216
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:19,880
Yeah, I'll be sure to pay you back.

217
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:22,720
You'll do unpaid chores for a year.

218
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:25,180
I'll let you off the hook with that.

219
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:27,430
A-A year?!

220
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:29,260
A-A year...

221
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:31,390
You mean a whole year?!

222
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,070
What's taking Luffy so long?

223
00:14:42,070 --> 00:14:43,650
Seriously...

224
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:47,620
Maybe they'll make him
do chores for a month or so.

225
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:52,080
He should've pinned it on the Marines,
that simple, honest fool.

226
00:15:09,470 --> 00:15:10,760
Hey, look.

227
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:14,440
Just as I thought, the man
sitting there is Lieutenant Fullbody.

228
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:16,650
He's a lieutenant from
Marine Headquarters.

229
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:17,400
– Huh?
– Huh?

230
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:20,150
He's wonderful. How elegant.

231
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:23,570
It's amazing.
Everyone's looking at you.

232
00:15:23,570 --> 00:15:26,450
Actually, they're admiring you.

233
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,080
Superb!

234
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:36,540
Th-This flavor...

235
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,250
This aroma...

236
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:43,260
It has a hint of the soil
from Micqueot, the Northlands.

237
00:15:43,260 --> 00:15:46,720
Lightly acidic, full-bodied, and dry...

238
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:49,260
This wine is...

239
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:52,680
Ithürzburger Stein!

240
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:56,520
Isn't that right, waiter?!

241
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:58,440
That's...

242
00:15:59,060 --> 00:16:00,400
damn wrong,

243
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:01,650
sir.

244
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,900
Your soup is getting cold.

245
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,530
Please eat it while it's hot.

246
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:14,500
By the way, I'm Sanji, the sous chef.

247
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:19,000
All the waiters ran off yesterday.

248
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:26,800
You shouldn't laugh.

249
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,890
But he looked so confident!

250
00:16:31,430 --> 00:16:32,470
Do you know a lot...

251
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:35,220
about wine?

252
00:16:36,230 --> 00:16:37,480
Well, yeah...

253
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:40,690
although it seems my
palate is a bit off today...

254
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:44,150
Hey, what's going on?

255
00:16:44,150 --> 00:16:48,820
I definitely asked the owner to serve us
that wine when I made the reservation.

256
00:16:53,410 --> 00:16:55,620
Please reduce it to a week.

257
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:58,580
You've gotta be kidding me.

258
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:00,000
Two weeks!

259
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:00,870
Hey!

260
00:17:00,870 --> 00:17:04,960
You wrecked my restaurant and
seriously injured me, the head chef.

261
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:09,630
You can't settle that with just
one or two weeks of unpaid work.

262
00:17:09,630 --> 00:17:11,470
Alright then! Three weeks!

263
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:14,140
Stop...

264
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:20,390
kidding around!

265
00:17:28,070 --> 00:17:28,940
No!

266
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:34,280
I've waited ten long years
to become a pirate.

267
00:17:34,950 --> 00:17:38,370
I definitely don't want
to be stuck here for another year!

268
00:17:39,370 --> 00:17:41,210
Okay, I've decided.

269
00:17:41,210 --> 00:17:43,290
I'll get you to let me
off the hook in a week.

270
00:17:43,290 --> 00:17:44,750
That's my decision.

271
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:45,630
Oh?

272
00:17:45,630 --> 00:17:48,340
If you value time so much,

273
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:52,550
I'll tell you what you can do
to settle it quickly.

274
00:17:54,930 --> 00:17:56,640
Hand over...

275
00:17:57,260 --> 00:17:58,640
one of your legs.

276
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:01,730
No!

277
00:18:02,730 --> 00:18:04,770
You've gotta be kidding me!

278
00:18:14,910 --> 00:18:16,370
Waiter!

279
00:18:20,950 --> 00:18:24,170
Didn't I tell you that I'm not a waiter?

280
00:18:26,790 --> 00:18:30,050
But my, how beautiful you are!

281
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:34,970
Say, miss, would you like to have
some wine with me over there?

282
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:37,470
Hey!

283
00:18:37,470 --> 00:18:41,430
What kind of restaurant serves
soup with bugs in it?!

284
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:42,930
Bugs?

285
00:18:42,930 --> 00:18:46,100
What the hell is this bug?!

286
00:18:47,310 --> 00:18:50,150
This will torpedo
this restaurant's reputation!

287
00:18:50,820 --> 00:18:52,820
I'm dreadfully sorry, sir,

288
00:18:52,820 --> 00:18:54,030
but I'm at a loss.

289
00:18:54,780 --> 00:18:59,080
I don't know much about insects.

290
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:12,760
Don't mess with me!

291
00:19:25,730 --> 00:19:29,690
You could've eaten it had you taken
that bug out, couldn't you?

292
00:19:30,070 --> 00:19:35,110
I spent three days and nights
on this soup, skimming the scum.

293
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:40,490
Aren't you acting a bit
too big for your britches?

294
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:44,790
I'm a customer!

295
00:19:44,790 --> 00:19:46,960
A paying customer!

296
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,580
Fullbody, please stop!

297
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:49,630
Shut up!

298
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,000
F-Fullbody...

299
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:55,510
Can money...

300
00:19:56,170 --> 00:19:58,220
satisfy your hunger?

301
00:19:58,220 --> 00:19:59,510
What was that?!

302
00:19:59,890 --> 00:20:01,600
I'm asking you...

303
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:05,020
Can it satisfy your hunger?!

304
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:06,730
No!

305
00:20:06,730 --> 00:20:07,560
No!

306
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:08,480
No!

307
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:15,740
Don't think that you can survive
by repeating "no," kid.

308
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,450
No!

309
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,910
You're kidding me!

310
00:20:34,130 --> 00:20:35,460
F-Fullbody...

311
00:20:36,170 --> 00:20:37,840
Sanji...

312
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,340
Sous Chef!

313
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,850
A fight?

314
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:53,860
Don't...

315
00:20:53,860 --> 00:20:56,190
waste food.

316
00:20:59,570 --> 00:21:01,990
Remember this:

317
00:21:02,450 --> 00:21:07,000
Crossing a cook at sea
is tantamount to suicide.

318
00:21:15,710 --> 00:21:16,880
I can't... hold it anymore...

319
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:18,050
Serving customers...

320
00:21:18,050 --> 00:21:19,380
equals "love"!

321
00:21:19,380 --> 00:21:21,590
And "love" equals "restaurant"!

322
00:21:21,590 --> 00:21:22,970
The customer...

323
00:21:22,970 --> 00:21:24,810
is king!

324
00:21:25,140 --> 00:21:27,930
Motto! Motto! It's my service motto!

325
00:21:27,930 --> 00:21:30,770
A pleasant greeting equals service!

326
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:33,400
Welcome, ya damn crook.

327
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:35,110
Please never come back.

328
00:21:35,110 --> 00:21:37,030
I'm terribly sorry.

329
00:21:37,030 --> 00:21:38,650
Ten thousand berries coming in!

330
00:21:38,650 --> 00:21:40,360
You look pathetic!

331
00:21:42,780 --> 00:21:43,700
Alright!

332
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:47,240
I took a healthy dump,
so I'm doing great today!

333
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:50,000
Oh? Welcome, ya damn crook.

334
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:53,080
Motto! Motto! It's my service motto!

335
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:54,500
The customer is–

336
00:21:55,210 --> 00:21:57,000
Our customer!

337
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,380
Back at it again, Sanji?!

338
00:21:59,380 --> 00:22:01,220
What are you doing to our customer?!

339
00:22:02,090 --> 00:22:05,050
And he's a Marine lieutenant to boot!

340
00:22:05,050 --> 00:22:06,810
What is it, you crappy cook?!

341
00:22:06,810 --> 00:22:09,430
Don't say my name as if we're friends.

342
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:13,770
Don't call me a crappy cook,
ya crappy cook!

343
00:22:13,770 --> 00:22:16,190
Restaurants rely on customers!

344
00:22:16,190 --> 00:22:18,530
Hurting our precious customer...

345
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:20,240
What do you think you're doing?!

346
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,700
So what if he's a customer?

347
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:27,490
He wasted his food
and insulted the cooks.

348
00:22:31,290 --> 00:22:33,870
So I taught him a lesson.

349
00:22:35,920 --> 00:22:38,550
Wh-What's with this restaurant?!

350
00:22:38,550 --> 00:22:43,010
No restaurant should
treat its customers like this.

351
00:22:43,010 --> 00:22:44,890
I'll shut it down...

352
00:22:44,890 --> 00:22:47,760
I'll shut this restaurant down!

353
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:48,970
I'll shut it all down!

354
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:51,730
I'll contact the government
immediately and...

355
00:22:52,890 --> 00:22:56,520
Then I'd better finish you off here.

356
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,190
Stop it, Sous Chef!

357
00:22:59,190 --> 00:23:04,860
Just looking at an arrogant blowhard
like you makes my blood boil!

358
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:00,900
What are you doing?!

359
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:03,150
Keep it up, and we'll be in big trouble!

360
00:23:03,150 --> 00:23:04,860
Stop it, Sanji!

361
00:23:04,860 --> 00:23:06,870
Stop it! You're going too far, Sanji!

362
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:11,490
So you think you're
a big shot?! Huh?!

363
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:20,090
Oh, boy...

364
00:23:20,090 --> 00:23:21,170
What happened?

365
00:23:21,170 --> 00:23:22,920
What now?

366
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:25,510
Man... that surprised me!

367
00:23:25,930 --> 00:23:28,260
Ch-Chef Zeff! What the heck
are you doing?!

368
00:23:28,260 --> 00:23:30,390
Oh, dammit!

369
00:23:30,390 --> 00:23:32,220
My restaurant's ceiling!

370
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:35,600
This is your fault, you brat!

371
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,560
You broke it yourself!

372
00:23:37,560 --> 00:23:39,560
What are you doing, Chef Zeff?!

373
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:42,650
Please help us stop Sanji first!

374
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:45,200
Hey, Sanji!

375
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:49,870
Are you going on a rampage
in the restaurant again, you idiot?!

376
00:23:49,870 --> 00:23:51,740
Shut up, you old fart!

377
00:23:51,740 --> 00:23:54,580
What'd you say?! Who do
you think you're talking to?!

378
00:23:54,580 --> 00:23:58,000
Are you trying to put
my restaurant out of business?!

379
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,880
You brat!

380
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,500
You, too!

381
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:03,960
Get out of here already!

382
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:12,220
What's with this restaurant?

383
00:24:12,220 --> 00:24:15,350
Even the head chef...
Their terrible attitudes are like...

384
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:16,600
It's as if...

385
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:19,230
as if... this were a pirate ship!

386
00:24:19,230 --> 00:24:21,690
Listen up! The customer is king!

387
00:24:21,980 --> 00:24:25,610
Just those who eat
your damn crappy dishes.

388
00:24:25,610 --> 00:24:26,990
Patty! Sanji!

389
00:24:26,990 --> 00:24:29,360
If you wanna fight,
do it in the kitchen!

390
00:24:30,490 --> 00:24:33,330
Are they really cooks?!

391
00:24:33,330 --> 00:24:34,700
L-Lieutenant!

392
00:24:35,370 --> 00:24:36,870
Lieutenant Fullbody!

393
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:40,880
W-We've got trouble!

394
00:24:41,460 --> 00:24:43,630
Man, what a wild restaurant.

395
00:24:43,630 --> 00:24:47,260
Krieg's underling escaped!

396
00:24:47,260 --> 00:24:48,220
What?!

397
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:53,720
After seven of us finally captured him
to get a lead on the Krieg Pirates...

398
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:54,930
No way!

399
00:24:54,930 --> 00:24:58,560
When we captured him three days ago
he was on the brink of starvation!

400
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:00,900
And we haven't fed him at all since!

401
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:03,860
Th-The Krieg Pirates?!

402
00:25:03,860 --> 00:25:07,150
Aren't they the strongest pirates
in the East Blue?!

403
00:25:07,150 --> 00:25:08,320
I'm very–

404
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,670
We have a new customer.

405
00:25:23,670 --> 00:25:27,840
He'd better not go trashing my place.

406
00:25:28,380 --> 00:25:29,840
A pirate, huh?

407
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:46,400
You can bring me anything
as long as it's food.

408
00:25:48,610 --> 00:25:50,780
This is a restaurant, right?

409
00:25:50,780 --> 00:25:53,280
Welcome, ya damn crook.

410
00:25:54,490 --> 00:25:57,120
I'll only say it once more,
so listen good.

411
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,790
Bring me food.

412
00:25:58,790 --> 00:26:00,910
That cook is gonna get killed...

413
00:26:00,910 --> 00:26:05,540
Um, sir, I'm terribly sorry,
but how will you be paying?

414
00:26:09,050 --> 00:26:10,380
Would a bullet do?

415
00:26:10,380 --> 00:26:12,220
So you don't have money, right?

416
00:26:13,090 --> 00:26:14,010
What?!

417
00:26:14,010 --> 00:26:16,470
Patty, that dumbass!
He broke the chair.

418
00:26:16,470 --> 00:26:18,060
Wow, he's strong!

419
00:26:19,850 --> 00:26:23,480
If you can't pay for the food,
you're not a customer.

420
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,110
Good job, cook!

421
00:26:25,110 --> 00:26:28,190
Beat that pirate up, Patty!

422
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:33,400
Oh... Your stomach
is grumbling, pirate.

423
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:36,280
That was a fart, you stupid tanuki.

424
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:38,950
Just bring me some food.

425
00:26:38,950 --> 00:26:41,410
If you're not a customer, then beat it!

426
00:26:47,290 --> 00:26:49,800
I-I've had enough already!

427
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,260
I want nothing to do
with this restaurant!

428
00:26:52,260 --> 00:26:55,140
I-I'll never come back here!

429
00:27:00,140 --> 00:27:02,180
Now, dear customers,

430
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:05,310
please continue your meal!

431
00:27:09,650 --> 00:27:11,440
Please never come back.

432
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:17,570
D-Dammit...

433
00:27:17,570 --> 00:27:20,580
Normally, that bastard
couldn't have even touched me...

434
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:32,340
Dig in.

435
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:44,230
The ocean is vast and cruel.

436
00:27:44,730 --> 00:27:49,730
I understand how scary it is
to have no food or water at sea.

437
00:27:50,230 --> 00:27:51,980
How hard it is.

438
00:27:53,780 --> 00:27:57,160
I know what hunger feels like
more than anyone.

439
00:27:58,780 --> 00:28:01,160
You can die for
your pride if you want,

440
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:02,790
but if you eat and survive,

441
00:28:02,790 --> 00:28:05,120
you'll live to see tomorrow, right?

442
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,010
I'm so ashamed.

443
00:28:21,890 --> 00:28:23,180
Sorry...

444
00:28:23,180 --> 00:28:24,680
Thank you...

445
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:26,100
I thought I was gonna die.

446
00:28:26,100 --> 00:28:28,350
I thought I was done for.

447
00:28:33,070 --> 00:28:34,070
Delicious...

448
00:28:34,070 --> 00:28:35,530
It's so delicious.

449
00:28:35,530 --> 00:28:39,240
I've never eaten food so delicious.

450
00:28:43,830 --> 00:28:45,200
It's damn tasty, isn't it?

451
00:28:47,210 --> 00:28:49,540
I found a good cook!

452
00:28:50,250 --> 00:28:54,340
Hey, you're lucky he gave you food!

453
00:28:55,260 --> 00:28:56,840
You almost died!

454
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:58,220
Hey you, cook!

455
00:28:58,220 --> 00:29:00,470
Join my crew!

456
00:29:02,050 --> 00:29:04,260
Be the cook on my pirate ship!

457
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:05,810
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

